3. The estimated financial statements of the target entity referred to in paragraph 1 shall, on
both an individual and, where applicable, a consolidated basis, for a period of three years,
include the following:
(a) a forecast balance sheet and income statement;
(b) forecast prudential capital requirements and reserve of assets;
(c) information on forecasted level of risk exposures including market, operational (such as
cyber and fraud), credit and environmental risks as well as other relevant risks;
(d) a forecast of provisional intra-group transactions.

